BRIEFING:
HNL DEP GATE A19
MILITARY EXERCISE SENTRY ALOHA 1/27-2/12
LIGHT WINDS WILL PREVAIL TODAY AND TONIGHT, ALLOWING SEA AND LAND BREEZES TO BE COMMON ACROSS THE STATE. AN AREA OF ENHANCED MOISTURE WILL KEEP SOME SHOWERS AND MVFR CIGS/VSBYS MOVING INTO WINDWARD AREAS THIS MORNING, WITH IMPROVING CONDITIONS EXPECTED IN MOST AREAS BY LATE MORNING OR EARLY AFTERNOON.
AIRMET SIERRA REMAINS IN EFFECT FOR MOUNTAIN OBSCURATION FOR WINDWARD SECTIONS OF OAHU, MOLOKAI, MAUI AND BIG ISLAND.
SIGMET XRAY FL240-FL350 COVERS AN AREA OF SEVERE TURB OCCURRING ACROSS THE EASTERN END OF THE STATE. THE AREA OF SEVERE TURB SHOULD WEAKEN TO MODERATE LEVELS LATER THIS MORNING, AND AIRMET TANGO WILL BE ISSUED TO REPLACE THE SIGMET AT THAT TIME.
